1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper discusses the use of the watershed algorithm for natural images, which is a common application in computer vision. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a new approach to the watershed algorithm using flooding graphs and pruning operators, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper discusses the use of the watershed algorithm for image segmentation, which is a common application in graphics. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses the use of lexicographic distance functions to extract watershed partitions, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning. 
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper involves the use of numerical methods to compute the watershed algorithm on edge or node weighted graphs.
